                            <comment id="14477573" author="paulk" created="Tue, 6 Nov 2007 04:38:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;p 209 of GINA states that list.property is equal to:&lt;br/&gt;
list.collect&lt;/p&gt;
{ item -&amp;gt; item?.property }
&lt;p&gt;i.e. is the same as list*.property if property isn&apos;t a property of list itself.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If this is indeed the case, then we should change DGM.getAt(Collection, String) from:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;           &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (value &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;instanceof&lt;/span&gt; Collection) {
               answer.addAll((Collection) value);
           } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
               answer.add(value);
           }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;           answer.add(value);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I.e. we should remove the flattening behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463573" author="guillaume" created="Tue, 6 Nov 2007 05:46:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds coherent to me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
